{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "Consider each point in our data set X to be a vertex (a 0-simplex).",
    "We can define a set of 1-simplices as connections between pairs of vertices, 2-simplices between collections of three vertices, and so on.",
    "Thus, we build a simplicial complex K that gives some sense of \"connectivity\" between data points.",
    "It can be thought of as a hyper-graph on X.",
    "Note that K is not necessarily unique on X."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}